methods.name: GetAnimatedAttributeCurveName
methods.doc: Get the animated attribute curve name at the specified index.

methods.name: GetAnimatedAttributeCurveNames
methods.doc: Get all animated attribute curve names.

methods.name: GetAnimatedAttributeCurveNamesCount
methods.doc: Return the number of animated attribute curve names this anim sequence drives. Curves are FRichCurve of type float.

methods.name: GetAnimatedAttributeStepCurveName
methods.doc: Get the animated attribute step curve name at the specified index.

methods.name: GetAnimatedAttributeStepCurveNames
methods.doc: Get all animated attribute step curve names.

methods.name: GetAnimatedAttributeStepCurveNamesCount
methods.doc: Return the number of animated attribute step curve names this anim sequence drives.

methods.name: GetAnimatedMaterialCurveSuffixe
methods.doc: Get the animated material curve suffix with the specified index.

methods.name: GetAnimatedMaterialCurveSuffixes
methods.doc: Get all animated material curve suffixes.

methods.name: GetAnimatedMaterialCurveSuffixesCount
methods.doc: Return the number of animated material curve suffixes this anim sequence drives. Curves are FRichCurve of type float.

methods.name: GetCustomAddCurveMetadataToSkeleton
methods.doc:
Get the custom attribute AddCurveMetadataToSkeleton. Return false if the attribute is not set.

Note - If this setting is disabled, curve metadata will be added to skeletal meshes for morph targets, but no metadata entry will be created for general curves.

methods.name: GetCustomDeleteExistingCustomAttributeCurves
methods.doc:
Get the custom attribute DeleteExistingCustomAttributeCurves. Return false if the attribute is not set.

Note - If true, all previous custom attribute curves are deleted if you reimport.

methods.name: GetCustomDeleteExistingMorphTargetCurves
methods.doc:
Get the custom attribute DeleteExistingMorphTargetCurves. Return false if the attribute is not set.

Note: If true, all previous morph target curves are deleted if you reimport.

methods.name: GetCustomDeleteExistingNonCurveCustomAttributes
methods.doc:
Get the custom attribute DeleteExistingNonCurveCustomAttributes. Return false if the attribute is not set.

Note - If true, all previous non-curve custom attributes are deleted if you reimport.

methods.name: GetCustomDoNotImportCurveWithZero
methods.doc:
Get the custom attribute DoNotImportCurveWithZero. Return false if the attribute is not set.

Note - If this attribute is enabled, only curves that have a value other than zero will be imported. This is to avoid adding extra curves to evaluate.

methods.name: GetCustomImportAttributeCurves
methods.doc:
Get the import attribute curves state. If true, all user custom attributes on nodes are imported.

Return false if the attribute is not set.

methods.name: GetCustomImportBoneTracks
methods.doc:
Get the import bone tracks state. If the attribute is true, bone tracks are imported. If the attribute
is false, bone tracks are not imported.

Return false if the attribute is not set. Return true if the attribute exists and can be queried.

methods.name: GetCustomImportBoneTracksRangeStart
methods.doc: Get the import bone tracks start time in seconds. Return false if the attribute is not set.

methods.name: GetCustomImportBoneTracksRangeStop
methods.doc: Get the import bone tracks end time in seconds. Return false if the attribute is not set.

methods.name: GetCustomImportBoneTracksSampleRate
methods.doc: Get the import bone tracks sample rate. Return false if the attribute is not set.

methods.name: GetCustomMaterialDriveParameterOnCustomAttribute
methods.doc:
Get the custom attribute MaterialDriveParameterOnCustomAttribute. Return false if the attribute is not set.

Note: If true, sets Material Curve Type for all custom attributes.

methods.name: GetCustomRemoveCurveRedundantKeys
methods.doc: Get the custom attribute RemoveCurveRedundantKeys. Return false if the attribute is not set.

methods.name: GetCustomSkeletonFactoryNodeUid
methods.doc: Get the unique ID of the skeleton factory node. Return false if the attribute is not set.

methods.name: GetCustomSkeletonSoftObjectPath
methods.doc:
Query the optional existing USkeleton this animation must use. If this attribute is set and the skeleton is valid,
the AnimSequence factory uses this skeleton instead of the one imported from GetCustomSkeletonFactoryNodeUid.
Pipelines set this attribute when the user wants to specify an existing skeleton.
Return false if the attribute was not set.

methods.name: GetObjectClass
methods.doc: Get the class this node creates.

methods.name: SetCustomImportBoneTracks
methods.doc: Set the import bone tracks state. Pass true to import bone tracks, or false to not import bone tracks.

methods.name: SetCustomRemoveCurveRedundantKeys
